cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on face recognition techniques using data captured under low-quality conditions in the wild, which is a common problem in surveillance-based applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses deep learning-based approaches, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper introduces a generative adversarial network pre-training approach and fully convolutional architecture, which are related to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also explores the low-resolution face identification using a supervised discriminative learning approach, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of face recognition in non-ideal conditions, which is related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
